Package core

Class CheckersLogic

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.CheckersLogic
  • public class CheckersLogic
extends java.lang.Object
    CheckersLogic class provides the logic to the ui.CheckersUI class. It uses the core.Board class to represent the board and the core.Player class to represent the players. This class validates the user input and determines if the move is valid by throwing an IllegalArgumentException. The ui should catch the exception and display the error message to the user and prompt the user again. It is easier to do matrix operation with 0-7 for both rows and cols but the user input is 1-8 for rows and A-H for cols. User input needs to be translated to valid row and col numbers and vice versa for displaying pawns. UI Row is 1 - 8 UI Col is A - H Board Row is 0 - 7 Board Col is 0 - 7 1a = 0, 0
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jose Solis

      • getToken

        public java.lang.String getToken​(int row,
                                 int col)
        This method is used to get the token of the pawn at the specified row and column. Useful for printing the pawn to the ui. If there is no pawn at the specified row and column, then null is returned. The ui uses the null case to print an empty space with an underscore.
        Parameters:
        row - The row of the pawn.
        col - The column of the pawn.
        Returns:
        The token of the pawn at the specified row and column, returns null if there is no pawn at the specified row and column.

      • playerMove

        public boolean playerMove​(Direction direction,
                          int row,
                          java.lang.String col,
                          int newRow,
                          java.lang.String newCol)
                   throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        This method is used to validate user input and move the pawn in a specified direction. If the pawn made a capture AND the pawn can make another capture, returns true and the ui uses the true case to allow the user to move again.
        Parameters:
        direction - The direction to move the pawn.
        row - The row of the pawn to move.
        col - The column of the pawn to move.
        newRow - The row to move the pawn to.
        newCol - The column to move the pawn to.
        Returns:
        True if the pawn made a capture AND the pawn can make another capture, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the new position is not a valid position or is not empty.
